1
00:00:00,200 --> 00:00:03,000
Wait, UPI can do this?

2
00:00:03,100 --> 00:00:07,400
Build one vertical template, not ten timelines.

3
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:12,000
Lock 1080 by 1920 once and keep the safe zones fixed.

4
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:17,000
Hooks, lower-thirds, stickers, and CTA stay swappable.

5
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:22,300
That means faster edits and fewer layout mistakes.

6
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:27,500
Write one English master script with tight caption timing.

7
00:00:27,600 --> 00:00:33,000
Translate the SRT, not the whole edit, into Tamil and Hindi.

8
00:00:33,100 --> 00:00:39,000
Generate matching TTS for each language at 48 kHz.

9
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:45,000
Then render three localized MP4s from the same picture-lock.

10
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:51,600
The payoff is simple: standardize once and scale daily.

11
00:00:51,700 --> 00:00:56,400
Tamil, English, and Hindi all ship from one job.

12
